 Police last night arrested 30 boys and girls at a house in Chepngaina village in Bomet County while allegedly engaging in illegal activities at a night party. ALSO READ:

Three KCSE candidates die Bomet Township Chief Rueben Ngetich said some students were drinking alcohol, dancing and others kissing as the music played in the background when police stormed the house. Used condoms were also found in the house. Police say most of those who arrested are candidates who recently completed their Kenya Certificate of Secondary Education (KCSE) examination. 15 girls are from Njerian Secondary School in Bomet. The woman suspected to have supplied the students with alcohol and food during the night party was also arrested as four other students managed to escape. Know if news is factual and true. Text 'NEWS' to 22840 and always receive verified news updates.